UNITED NATIONS , February 10 -LRB- Xinhua -RRB- -- U.N. Secretary - General Kofi Annan on Tuesday strongly condemned a `` brutal and Cowardly '' terrorist attack against Georgian President Eduard Shevardnadze .
`` The Secretary - General has condemned terrorism in any form and stresses that such acts of violence cannot possibly serve any national or political cause , '' Annan 's spokesman said in a statement .
Attackers ambushed Shevardnadze 's motorcade with anti-tank grenade launchers and guns on Monday , leaving his two bodyguards dead while one of the attackers was killed .
The president , who escaped unharmed , said he did not rule out the possibility of this being `` a manifestation of international terrorism '' , according to press reports .
